hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: I'd like to send this parcel to farmacia247.com Duchamp came to Kent to chaperone his 18-year-old sister Yvonne. Earlier that year, his Modernist painting Nude Descending a Staircase had caused a scandal at the Armory Show in New York. Derided by one critic as “an explosion in a shingle factory”, its fractured forms were scornfully compared by Theodore Roosevelt to a Navajo rug. “I am very depressed at the moment and do absolutely nothing,” Duchamp wrote in July 1913. “I am going away in August to spend some time in England.”
